@startuml Memory Forensics - Complete System Sequence Diagram

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam BoxPadding 10

title Memory Forensics Automation Tool - Complete System Flow

actor "Forensic Analyst" as User
box "Frontend (Flutter Desktop)" #LightBlue
    participant "Dashboard\nScreen" as Dashboard
    participant "Upload\nScreen" as Upload
    participant "Case\nRepository" as Repo
end box

box "Backend API (Flask)" #LightGreen
    participant "Flask\nAPI Server" as API
    participant "Cases\nRoute" as Route
    participant "File\nHandler" as FileHandler
end box

box "Data Layer" #LightYellow
    database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB
    participant "File\nSystem" as FS
    participant "Redis\nQueue" as Redis
end box

box "Background Processing" #LightCoral
    participant "RQ\nWorker" as Worker
    participant "analyze_memory_dump\nTask" as Task
    participant "Volatility3\nCLI Tool" as VolCLI
end box

box "Analysis Engine" #LightPink
    participant "Format\nDetector" as Format
    participant "OS\nDetector" as OSDetect
    participant "Plugin\nExecutor" as PluginExec
    participant "Report\nGenerator" as Reporter
end box

== 1. Case Creation & File Upload ==

User -> Dashboard: Open application
activate Dashboard
Dashboard -> User: Display dashboard with statistics
User -> Dashboard: Click "Upload Case"
Dashboard -> Upload: Navigate to upload screen
deactivate Dashboard
activate Upload

User -> Upload: Drag & drop memory dump file\n(.raw, .mem, .vmem, .bin)
Upload -> Upload: Validate file extension
Upload -> Upload: Display file name and size

User -> Upload: Enter case name & description
User -> Upload: Click "Upload"

Upload -> Repo: uploadCase(file, name, description)
activate Repo

Repo -> API: POST /api/cases/upload\n(multipart/form-data)
activate API

API -> Route: handle_upload_request()
activate Route

Route -> Route: Validate file type\nValidate case name\nValidate file size

Route -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
activate DB

Route -> DB: INSERT INTO cases\n(name, description, status='queued',\npriority=5, created_at=NOW())
DB --> Route: case_id (e.g., 25)

Route -> FileHandler: save_file(file, case_id)
activate FileHandler

FileHandler -> FS: Create directory\ndata/cases/{case_id}/
activate FS
FS --> FileHandler: Directory created
deactivate FS

FileHandler -> FS: Save file with secure filename
activate FS
FS --> FileHandler: File saved at path
deactivate FS

FileHandler -> FileHandler: Calculate SHA-256 checksum\n(read in 4KB chunks)

FileHandler -> DB: INSERT INTO case_files\n(case_id, file_path, file_size,\nchecksum, mime_type, stored_at)
activate DB
DB --> FileHandler: file_id
deactivate DB

FileHandler --> Route: file_metadata\n{path, size, checksum}
deactivate FileHandler

Route -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
deactivate DB

== 2. Asynchronous Job Enqueue ==

Route -> Redis: task_queue.enqueue(\nanalyze_memory_dump,\ncase_id=25,\njob_timeout='2h',\nresult_ttl=86400)
activate Redis

Redis -> Redis: Create job with unique ID
Redis -> Redis: Store job in queue:\n'forensics_analysis'

Redis --> Route: job_id (e.g., "abc123...")
deactivate Redis

Route --> API: Response:\n{\n  "message": "Case created",\n  "case": {case_object},\n  "job": {\n    "job_id": "abc123",\n    "status": "queued"\n  }\n}
deactivate Route

API --> Repo: HTTP 201 Created\n{case_id, job_id, status}
deactivate API

Repo --> Upload: Upload successful
deactivate Repo

Upload -> Dashboard: Navigate to dashboard
deactivate Upload
activate Dashboard

Dashboard -> User: Show success notification:\n"Case created successfully\nAnalysis job queued"
deactivate Dashboard

== 3. Background Worker Processing ==

note over Worker
    Worker continuously polls
    Redis queue for jobs
end note

Worker -> Redis: Poll for jobs from\n'forensics_analysis' queue
activate Worker
activate Redis

Redis --> Worker: Job: analyze_memory_dump\n{case_id: 25}
deactivate Redis

Worker -> Task: Execute task(case_id=25)
activate Task

Task -> DB: SELECT * FROM cases\nWHERE id=25
activate DB
DB --> Task: case_data\n{id, name, status, files}
deactivate DB

Task -> DB: UPDATE cases\nSET status='processing',\nupdated_at=NOW()\nWHERE id=25
activate DB
DB --> Task: Updated
deactivate DB

Task -> DB: SELECT file_path FROM case_files\nWHERE case_id=25
activate DB
DB --> Task: file_path:\n"data/cases/25/dump.raw"
deactivate DB

== 4. Memory Dump Analysis ==

Task -> Format: detect_dump_format(file_path)
activate Format

Format -> FS: Read file header (512 bytes)
activate FS
FS --> Format: header_bytes
deactivate FS

Format -> Format: Check magic bytes:\n- PAGEDUMP (Windows crash)\n- ELF (Linux core)\n- LIME, VMware, etc.

Format --> Task: FormatInfo:\n{\n  type: "Raw",\n  confidence: "HIGH",\n  evidence: [...]\n}
deactivate Format

Task -> OSDetect: enhanced_os_detection(file_path)
activate OSDetect

OSDetect -> FS: Read sample (4MB)
activate FS
FS --> OSDetect: sample_data
deactivate FS

OSDetect -> OSDetect: Scan for signatures:\n- Windows: "SystemRoot", "KDBG"\n- Linux: "Linux version"\n- Calculate confidence scores

OSDetect --> Task: OSInfo:\n{\n  os_type: "Windows",\n  version: "Windows 10",\n  confidence: "HIGH"\n}
deactivate OSDetect

Task -> Task: Select plugins based on OS:\n- windows.pslist\n- windows.netscan\n- windows.cmdline\n- windows.dlllist

== 5. Volatility Plugin Execution ==

Task -> PluginExec: run_plugins_parallel(\nplugins, file_path,\nmax_workers=4)
activate PluginExec

loop For each plugin (parallel execution)
    PluginExec -> VolCLI: Execute:\nvol -f dump.raw\nwindows.pslist
    activate VolCLI
    
    VolCLI -> FS: Read and analyze\nmemory structures
    activate FS
    FS --> VolCLI: Memory data
    deactivate FS
    
    VolCLI -> VolCLI: Parse process structures\nExtract PIDs, names, PPIDs
    
    VolCLI --> PluginExec: Plugin output (text)
    deactivate VolCLI
end

PluginExec -> PluginExec: Parse all plugin outputs\nExtract structured data

PluginExec --> Task: Parsed results:\n{\n  processes: [...],\n  network: [...],\n  dlls: [...]\n}
deactivate PluginExec

== 6. Report Generation ==

Task -> Reporter: generate_report(\ncase_id, results,\nfile_metadata)
activate Reporter

Reporter -> Reporter: Build report structure:\n- Summary\n- System info\n- Process list\n- Network connections\n- Analysis metadata

Reporter -> Reporter: Format as JSON

Reporter -> FS: Save report to:\ndata/cases/25/report.json
activate FS
FS --> Reporter: Report saved
deactivate FS

Reporter --> Task: report_path:\n"data/cases/25/report.json"
deactivate Reporter

== 7. Update Case Status ==

Task -> DB: UPDATE cases\nSET status='completed',\nmetadata='{...}',\nupdated_at=NOW()\nWHERE id=25
activate DB
DB --> Task: Updated
deactivate DB

Task -> DB: UPDATE case_files\nSET report_path='...'\nWHERE case_id=25
activate DB
DB --> Task: Updated
deactivate DB

Task --> Worker: Task completed successfully
deactivate Task

Worker -> Redis: Mark job as finished
activate Redis
Redis --> Worker: Job marked complete
deactivate Redis

Worker -> Worker: Log completion
deactivate Worker

== 8. Status Polling & Report Retrieval ==

note over User, Dashboard
    User periodically checks
    case status from dashboard
end note

User -> Dashboard: View case list
activate Dashboard

Dashboard -> Repo: getCases(page=1, limit=10)
activate Repo

Repo -> API: GET /api/cases/?page=1&limit=10
activate API

API -> DB: SELECT * FROM cases\nORDER BY created_at DESC\nLIMIT 10 OFFSET 0
activate DB
DB --> API: cases_list
deactivate DB

API --> Repo: HTTP 200 OK\n{cases: [...], pagination: {...}}
deactivate API

Repo --> Dashboard: List of cases
deactivate Repo

Dashboard -> User: Display cases with status:\n"Case 25: Completed ✓"

User -> Dashboard: Click on Case 25\nto view report

Dashboard -> Repo: getCaseReport(case_id=25)
activate Repo

Repo -> API: GET /api/cases/25/report
activate API

API -> DB: SELECT * FROM cases\nWHERE id=25
activate DB
DB --> API: case_data
deactivate DB

API -> FS: Read report.json
activate FS
FS --> API: report_content
deactivate FS

API --> Repo: HTTP 200 OK\n{report: {...}}
deactivate API

Repo --> Dashboard: CaseReport object
deactivate Repo

Dashboard -> User: Display analysis results:\n- System info\n- Processes (25 found)\n- Network connections (12)\n- Indicators
deactivate Dashboard

== 9. Error Handling (Alternative Flow) ==

note over Task, DB
    If analysis fails at any point
end note

Task -> DB: UPDATE cases\nSET status='failed',\nmetadata='{"error": "..."}'\nWHERE id=25
activate Task
activate DB
DB --> Task: Updated
deactivate DB

Task --> Worker: Task failed with error
deactivate Task

Worker -> Worker: Log error details
activate Worker
deactivate Worker

Dashboard -> User: Show error notification:\n"Analysis failed - see details"
activate Dashboard
deactivate Dashboard

@enduml
